# BERT-Based Models (General NLP tasks)
# "bert-base-uncased" - A standard BERT model (good for most tasks)
# "bert-large-uncased" - A larger version of BERT (higher accuracy but slower)
# "bert-base-cased" - BERT model with case sensitivity

# DistilBERT (Smaller, faster variant of BERT)
# "distilbert-base-uncased" - A smaller version of BERT, faster with decent accuracy
# "distilbert-base-cased" - Case-sensitive variant of DistilBERT

# RoBERTa (Improved BERT-based model)
# "roberta-base" - A popular variant of BERT with improved performance
# "roberta-large" - Larger version of RoBERTa (more accurate but slower)

# Longformer (For long documents, handles large context windows)
# "allenai/longformer-base-4096" - Longformer for processing long documents

# Sentence-BERT (For sentence embeddings, semantic search)
# "all-MiniLM-L6-v2" - Efficient sentence embeddings model
# "paraphrase-MiniLM-L6-v2" - Small and fast, ideal for paraphrase tasks
# "paraphrase-distilroberta-base-v1" - Another option for paraphrase and sentence-level tasks

# GPT Models (For advanced generation and embeddings)
# "gpt-3.5-turbo" - OpenAI's GPT-3.5 model for generation and embeddings (via API)
# "gpt-4" - OpenAI's GPT-4 model for more advanced tasks (via API)

# T5 (Text-to-Text model, useful for generation tasks like summarization)
# "t5-small" - A smaller version of T5 for text-to-text tasks
# "t5-base" - Standard T5 model for text generation tasks
# "t5-large" - Larger version of T5 with improved performance

# ALBERT (A smaller and faster variant of BERT)
# "albert-base-v2" - A smaller and efficient version of BERT
# "albert-large-v2" - Larger version with better performance but slower

# XLNet (Alternative to BERT with improved language modeling capabilities)
# "xlnet-base-cased" - XLNet model for tasks like text classification
# "xlnet-large-cased" - Larger variant of XLNet with better performance
